
COMMENDS:
	- DO SH SPANNING-TREE


Which switch is the root bridge?
	A. switch 3

Identify the role (root/designated/non-designated) of each switch port:
SW1 F0/1: N-D   F0/2: N-D    F0/3: R   F0/4: N-D

SW2 F0/1: D   F0/2:  D  F0/3: N-D   G0/1: R

SW3 F0/1: D    F0/2: D    F0/3: D   G0/1: D

SW4 G0/1: D   G0/2: R


RULES TO FOLLOW:

	* One switch is elected as the root bridge

		- ROOT Bridge Selection :
			+ Lowest Bridge ID
			+ If the Bridge ID's are the same :
				- The lowest mac address id become the root bridge
	
		- All port's on the root bridge are (D) designated ports
			+ Forwarding state


	* Each remaining switch will select one of it's interfaces to be it's ROOT Port (R)
		+ ROOT Port's (Forwarding State)
	
		- Root Port Selection :
			+ lowest root cost
			+ lowest neighbor bridge id
			+ lowest neighbor port id

		- Ports accross the root port are always designated ports (D)
			+ forwarding

	* Each remaining collision domain will select one interface to be a designated port (D),fowarding state, and the       
            other port in the collision domain will be non-designated (blocking state)

		- Designated port Selection :
			+ interface on witch with lowest root cost
			+ interface on switch with lowest bridge id
